\begin_body

\begin_layout Itemize
Found closed loops in the 8 parameter gains for wake and sleep by choosing
 the right plasticity windows.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Approximated velocities as Sine functions, with period of 8 hrs for sleep
 and 16 hrs for wake, i.e.:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
G(t) & = & sin(nt),\\
\dot{G(t)} & = & ncos(nt),
\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset

where period 
\begin_inset Formula $T=2\pi/n$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Therefore in phase space the velocity follows ellipses, between the min
 and max 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

.
 i.e.
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\dot{G}^{2}=n^{2}(1-\frac{G^{2}}{b^{2}}),
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $(G_{min}+G_{max})/2$
\end_inset

.
 (ellipses go through the origin).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\end_layout

\end_body
